1
00:00:36,240 --> 00:00:36,960
Yingtang

2
00:00:37,240 --> 00:00:38,159
Eat more

3
00:00:38,799 --> 00:00:39,520
Thanks, Mom

4
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:41,439
It's been so long since you came back

5
00:00:41,799 --> 00:00:42,679
You've gotten thinner

6
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:44,920
Studying at school must be hard work

7
00:00:46,960 --> 00:00:48,280
I have to take the preliminary college entrance exam soon

8
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:49,280
Mom

9
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:50,640
Can you give me some money?

10
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:52,920
What is the preliminary college entrance exam?

11
00:00:53,240 --> 00:00:53,880
How much do you need?

12
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:55,560
It's the exam before the Gaokao

13
00:00:55,960 --> 00:00:57,640
Only after passing it can I take the Gaokao

14
00:00:59,079 --> 00:01:00,159
Just give me a hundred first

15
00:01:00,520 --> 00:01:01,479
That much?

16
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:07,159
Little Sister

17
00:01:07,760 --> 00:01:09,480
Every time you come back, you just want money

18
00:01:09,719 --> 00:01:11,000
The tuition has already been paid

19
00:01:11,239 --> 00:01:12,920
Where do you need to spend so much money?

20
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,200
You haven't been to school anyway

21
00:01:15,799 --> 00:01:16,719
What do you know?

22
00:01:17,879 --> 00:01:18,439
That's right

23
00:01:18,719 --> 00:01:19,840
I haven't been to school

24
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:21,480
But I'm the one paying

25
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,200
Every time you ask for money

26
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:24,400
Mom tries every way possible

27
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,599
to make me and Eldest Sister pay

28
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:27,079
Mom

29
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,799
Look at Second Sister

30
00:01:29,239 --> 00:01:29,920
Number Two

31
00:01:30,079 --> 00:01:31,239
Watch your mouth

32
00:01:31,879 --> 00:01:32,599
Yingtang

33
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:34,599
is the most promising person in our family

34
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:36,359
She's about to take the college entrance exam

35
00:01:36,439 --> 00:01:37,200
You and the eldest

36
00:01:37,319 --> 00:01:39,200
won't you have to rely on her in the future?

37
00:01:39,519 --> 00:01:40,840
So what if you pay a little money?

38
00:01:41,079 --> 00:01:42,359
Let's talk about that after she gets in

39
00:01:43,079 --> 00:01:43,680
Besides

40
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,040
I'm not relying on her anyway

41
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:54,040
Let me make this clear first

42
00:01:54,319 --> 00:01:56,079
Eldest Sister and I don't have any money right now

43
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,079
If you want to give money

44
00:01:57,079 --> 00:01:58,280
you give it yourself

45
00:01:59,079 --> 00:01:59,560
Number Two

46
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:00,680
What do you mean?

47
00:02:01,159 --> 00:02:01,680
Come back

48
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:04,040
These machines

49
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:06,239
I brought them all back from Germany

50
00:02:06,439 --> 00:02:07,400
The parts

51
00:02:07,599 --> 00:02:09,120
are very precise

52
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,360
The German engineers

53
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:13,000
are very busy

54
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:14,960
If you wait for them to come debug the machines

55
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:17,159
that will take forever

56
00:02:18,039 --> 00:02:19,719
This is a private factory

57
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:21,960
There are so many machines

58
00:02:22,199 --> 00:02:24,120
We are the first one here

59
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:26,120
Sino-Hong Kong joint venture factory

60
00:02:26,439 --> 00:02:27,800
Although I am from Hong Kong, China

61
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:29,560
my hometown is right here

62
00:02:29,919 --> 00:02:31,560
I have feelings for this place

63
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:32,800
We...

64
00:02:33,199 --> 00:02:35,199
looked for many skilled workers

65
00:02:35,319 --> 00:02:37,039
but none could get these machines running

66
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,520
If you can help me

67
00:02:39,199 --> 00:02:40,840
you will be our Technical Consultant

68
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,719
As for the compensation

69
00:02:42,919 --> 00:02:43,520
rest assured

70
00:02:43,639 --> 00:02:45,240
I definitely won't treat you unfairly

71
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:46,800
You can rest assured about that

72
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:48,919
Fixing a machine...

73
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:50,719
I haven't been doing this for just a day or two

74
00:02:51,439 --> 00:02:53,080
It's just debugging a new machine, isn't it?

75
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:53,960
German machines

76
00:02:54,039 --> 00:02:55,039
I've handled them before too

77
00:02:55,479 --> 00:02:56,400
Let me give it a try

78
00:02:58,639 --> 00:02:59,759
He looks like he has some skill

79
00:02:59,759 --> 00:03:01,520
Is it okay to just go up there?

80
00:03:10,719 --> 00:03:12,080
Seems like he has some real skill

81
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,000
He looks quite professional

82
00:03:54,039 --> 00:03:54,840
Boss Tang

83
00:03:56,599 --> 00:03:57,319
Done

84
00:03:57,319 --> 00:03:58,120
See?

85
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,159
It really can be fixed

86
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:01,199
Chief, Chief

87
00:04:01,639 --> 00:04:02,759
Is it that fast?

88
00:04:02,879 --> 00:04:04,080
Wait a moment

89
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,039
This...

90
00:04:06,039 --> 00:04:06,800
is already fixed

91
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:07,599
Who am I?

92
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,280
I'm someone at the Chief level

93
00:04:09,439 --> 00:04:11,120
How could I not handle this?

94
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,639
What did I say?

95
00:04:15,719 --> 00:04:17,240
Piece of cake

96
00:04:17,319 --> 00:04:18,920
Calibration successful, Boss Tang

97
00:04:21,319 --> 00:04:21,839
Boss Tang

98
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,319
As we discussed earlier

99
00:04:25,319 --> 00:04:26,839
Thank you so much

100
00:04:26,959 --> 00:04:28,240
You got the machine calibrated

101
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:30,199
I'll arrange that payment for you right away

102
00:04:30,319 --> 00:04:31,480
Well, Boss Tang

103
00:04:31,959 --> 00:04:33,720
Since I'm the only one who can calibrate it

104
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,399
then regarding the payment

105
00:04:35,399 --> 00:04:37,120
it can't be two hundred yuan a day

106
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:37,879
It should be

107
00:04:37,879 --> 00:04:39,560
two hundred per machine

108
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,160
That's not expensive

109
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,040
The rate for German technicians

110
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:46,120
I know it well

111
00:04:46,639 --> 00:04:47,800
For every machine

112
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:48,839
they charge five hundred

113
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:50,439
And that's in US dollars

114
00:04:50,639 --> 00:04:51,560
True

115
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:53,240
That is indeed the case

116
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:56,040
Deal

117
00:04:56,279 --> 00:04:57,160
Your skills

118
00:04:57,439 --> 00:04:58,480
are indeed solid

119
00:04:58,639 --> 00:05:00,680
Then I'll leave the other machines to you

120
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:02,160
I'll get back to work then

121
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:04,759
Go notify everyone immediately

122
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,120
Their big orders

123
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:07,040
we're taking them all

124
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,319
Also, tell them

125
00:05:08,319 --> 00:05:09,759
we want to increase the orders

126
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:11,319
Let's get to work, let's get to work

127
00:05:11,319 --> 00:05:11,959
Get to work, get to work

128
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,160
Uncle Fang

129
00:05:17,319 --> 00:05:17,879
Smell this

130
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:18,759
See if this is it

131
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:43,439
Yingrong

132
00:05:43,839 --> 00:05:46,240
How was this vinegar stored?

133
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:49,199
Just right next to the kitchen stove

134
00:05:49,519 --> 00:05:50,160
What's wrong?

135
00:05:50,839 --> 00:05:52,199
That explains it

136
00:05:52,399 --> 00:05:53,279
This vinegar

137
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:54,800
is indeed Baliang Vinegar

138
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,759
But the flavor has faded a lot

139
00:05:57,160 --> 00:05:59,000
It must not have been sealed properly

140
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,040
And another thing is

141
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:02,199
it's due to long-term exposure to high heat

142
00:06:02,319 --> 00:06:03,360
It's a bit of a pity

143
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:07,439
Uncle Fang

144
00:06:07,759 --> 00:06:08,959
Give me a little more time

145
00:06:09,199 --> 00:06:09,959
I have a way

146
00:06:09,959 --> 00:06:10,759
I can try it out

147
00:06:27,319 --> 00:06:28,240
Zheng Xiaochuan

148
00:06:28,439 --> 00:06:30,040
You stole my motorcycle last time

149
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:31,399
What are you planning to do this time?

150
00:06:31,959 --> 00:06:32,439
Also

151
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,000
that motorcycle of mine

152
00:06:34,279 --> 00:06:35,480
when do you plan to pay me back for it?

153
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:36,560
Sister Yingrong

154
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:37,360
That motorcycle of yours

155
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:38,639
my big brother is fixing it right now

156
00:06:38,959 --> 00:06:39,720
With his skills

157
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:41,519
once it's fixed, it'll be better than new

158
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:43,079
Sister Yingrong

159
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:47,199
I heard your sister came back

160
00:06:47,279 --> 00:06:48,399
How come I didn't see her?

161
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:50,759
She went back to school

162
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,480
That big brother of yours

163
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:58,279
can he really fix the motorcycle?

164
00:06:58,600 --> 00:06:59,600
Of course

165
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:00,759
My big brother's skills

166
00:07:00,759 --> 00:07:02,319
he's loved tinkering with things since he was little

167
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:03,519
As long as it's a machine

168
00:07:03,519 --> 00:07:04,959
there's nothing he can't fix

169
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,480
That's true

170
00:07:10,279 --> 00:07:10,839
Where is he?

171
00:07:10,959 --> 00:07:11,680
I have something to ask him

172
00:07:24,839 --> 00:07:26,279
I didn't expect this vinegar workshop to still be here.

173
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,600
Ever since Uncle had his accident,

174
00:07:29,759 --> 00:07:31,480
this vinegar workshop has been sitting idle.

175
00:07:32,639 --> 00:07:34,160
Check and see if those machines still work.

176
00:07:39,199 --> 00:07:39,879
Be careful.

177
00:07:47,959 --> 00:07:49,160
The machines are fine.

178
00:07:50,199 --> 00:07:51,759
It's just that some parts have aged.

179
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:53,160
They should still be usable.

180
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,399
That's great.

181
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:59,199
If you can fix these machines,

182
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,759
I'll reconsider

183
00:08:01,879 --> 00:08:03,079
the compensation for the pigs.

184
00:08:05,319 --> 00:08:06,600
Fixing this is simple.

185
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:08,040
If we calculate it that way,

186
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:09,639
you're the one losing out.

187
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:11,399
Stop putting on airs.

188
00:08:11,839 --> 00:08:14,240
Have you, Zheng Minjiang, ever done a losing deal?

189
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,560
Isn't it always you scamming others?

190
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,560
I've never seen

191
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:19,839
anyone as petty as you.

192
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,600
But why do you need this machine fixed?

193
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:26,199
Uncle Fang wants Baliang Vinegar.

194
00:08:26,639 --> 00:08:27,480
But,

195
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:29,199
a batch of vinegar my Second Aunt left behind

196
00:08:29,199 --> 00:08:30,199
has oxidized a bit.

197
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:30,839
It just so happens

198
00:08:30,839 --> 00:08:31,920
she left some vinegar mash.

199
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,000
So I was thinking,

200
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:34,240
I'd take this vinegar and the vinegar mash,

201
00:08:34,559 --> 00:08:35,679
and distill them together.

202
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:38,200
You actually understand this?

203
00:08:38,399 --> 00:08:40,399
My Second Aunt told me a bit before she went mad.

204
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:43,639
You don't know anything,

205
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:44,799
yet you dare to do it.

206
00:08:45,559 --> 00:08:45,960
Hold this.

207
00:08:46,399 --> 00:08:48,480
It's because I don't know anything that I have to do it.

208
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:51,519
Who is born knowing everything?

209
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:52,720
You, Zheng Minjiang,

210
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:54,399
were you born knowing how to fix machines?

211
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:56,440
Isn't it all just trial and error?

212
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,559
You fix enough, and you learn.

213
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:00,960
Paths are made by walking.

214
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:02,159
Things get done by doing.

215
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:03,519
Just thinking is useless.

216
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,080
Besides,

217
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,480
I'm not that stupid.

218
00:09:06,639 --> 00:09:08,720
If it weren't for the problem with Second Aunt's batch,

219
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,360
I would have got the money long ago.

220
00:09:11,039 --> 00:09:11,960
Not bad.

221
00:09:12,399 --> 00:09:14,480
Your brain is working faster than last time.

222
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:15,519
You...

223
00:09:19,159 --> 00:09:20,639
My bad, I won't say anymore.

224
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:28,919
Pass me the toolbox.

225
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:28,679
Done.
